<br>
However I argue back the point for a warrior class  How many warriors in books add a notch to their weapon after some great accomplishment?<br>
<br>
Whereas my character (Enchantress) adds a Seduction everytime she feels she has progressed she goes out and tries to Seduce something a bit harder than before  when I hit 60 (yeah right) she will attempt to seduce Trakanon (again LOL). <br>
<br>
Personally I would like two more changes to make it harder on knowing level and items.<br>
First no examining other characters.  You gonna let someone come up and grab your hand and look at your rings or tell them the name of your Robe?  Hell how do they know I have a necklace without trying to take off my robes?  I am the seducer not the other way around.<br>
<br>
Second make pc's unable to con others.  I have already seen some light characters and dark characters getting buffed and trying to find people blue to them and challenging them to a duel.  Whereas I accepted a duel from someone conning yellow to me right after I noticed his cleric buffing him up and after he was healed there was a dark elf cleric friend of mine that tried to heal but think of it there was almost no chance of me finishing the fight after I used my mana on him.  He eventually left after I went to med invised <p>Teir'Dal Enchantress of the 11th Seduction.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 6:48:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Since its Roleplaying prefered....</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
1) Yes it is a little strange that level/class is forcibly hidden, and this is in the aid of RP. I don't think it helps RP or hinders it, but I do think it makes gameplay harder. But we will manage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2) 'OOC' chat inside hunting groups, or in tells or guildchat, can be part ofthe fun of the game. Sure, I love to Roleplay, but not every second, and not in the technical moments of communicating during a group fight. OOC spam in whole zones from strangers is just anti-roleplay environment, I feel. So I am happy with Verant's call to get rid of it. Now if they can just reduce the range on /auc in zones like GFay, and I'll be even happier. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3) /tells are fine. They can be RP or not RP, depending on the circumstances. Mine always start RP, but if needs must (or its a games mechanics issue), we can switch to ooc when needed. I'm happy.<br>
<br>
4) Human is too easy yes. It should be no easier than the other languages. I am enjoying the fun of the language barrier for the most part (yes I know it can be frustrating at times, but thats the challenge, I think). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So although I would prefer if 1) were different, I'm happy with 2, 3 and 4 as they are.<br>
<br>
As for Kaludram's number 5, I agree totally that, abusive language and behaviour is totally unacceptable, for whatever reason. I stress I exclude that from what I am about to say, as there is ZERO excuse for the personal harassment of others who are keeping themselves to themselves, absolutely zero.<br>
<br>
This stated, I am personally pleased to see roleplayers exert some pressure on the community to conform, in the way non-roleplayers pressure roleplayers to on other servers. We want to shape this place, and we want it to meet our dream. This is a positive thing for most of us, not a negative one. Stick and carrot can be used here, and I fully intend to use both. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And I congratulate and encourage fellow roleplayers to do the same, so we can make a world we can be proud of. Non-roleplayers should *never* be harassed for their choices, but if they find they are in the cold somewhat, they at least have so many others servers to choose from. We don't. Think about it before giving lectures please. <p>------------------------------------------------<BR><BR>
